title: Germanwings plane lost part of engine cladding at takeoff
text:
Germanwings plane lost part of engine cladding at takeoff Last updated 11:31, October 22 2015 Twitter 
Pilots did not notice that part of the engine cladding had fallen off until they were notified by air traffic controllers over France. 
Germanwings said one of its planes lost part of the cladding on its left engine during takeoff from Cologne. 
The company said the Airbus A330 departed for Palma on the Spanish island of Mallorca. 
It said the pilots did not notice that part of the engine cladding had fallen off until they were notified by air traffic controllers over France.
